description:
Problem:
The new documents leaf exists, but the schema and routing are still too weak for document subtypes. RFC-027 expects document questions by lamp name to support subtype-aware behavior such as passport/certificate/manual/IES instead of only a generic documents list.

Required changes:
- extend the documents leaf contract with an explicit document_type field and a compact enum such as passport/certificate/manual/ies;
- improve subtype detection for singular/plural and imperative phrasing (e.g. passport, certificate, manual, IES questions);
- ensure document questions by lamp name resolve to the documents family instead of drifting into company info or generic catalog leaves;
- add family-local document fallback from subtype-specific asks to broader documents-by-lamp behavior when subtype resolution is incomplete.

Acceptance criteria:
- schema for documents family exposes document_type as a route-local field where appropriate;
- queries like “Покажи паспорт на NL Nova” and “Покажи сертификат на NL Nova” route to the documents family and a valid documents leaf;
- generic “Какие документы есть для NL Nova?” still works;
- degraded/validation-tested behavior remains bounded inside the documents family;
- tests cover document subtypes and family-local fallback.

Problem:
RFC-027 expects a three-stage model. Specialized leafs should not be the only leaves available. Each stable family/table domain needs a broader stage-1_general route so the selector can still answer table/source-aligned questions that do not fit narrower stage-2 leafs.

Required changes:
- add or formalize broad/general leaves for the main families aligned to durable sources/tables;
- ensure each family has a clear fallback broad leaf (for example company general, catalog general/entity lookup, documents general, codes general, sphere mapping general, portfolio general, mountings general where applicable);
- wire the route tree so unmatched but still family-aligned questions land on the broad family leaf instead of drifting across unrelated families;
- keep route-local schemas narrow even for broad leaves.

Acceptance criteria:
- every major active business family has at least one broad stage-1_general leaf available to the selector;
- questions that do not fit specialized leaves but clearly belong to a family route to that family’s broad leaf;
- specialized leafs do not need to overfit generic questions that belong to the same source/table family;
- tests cover at least one broad fallback question per family.

Parent: totosha-7h9
RFC: docs/rfc/RFC-021-runtime-llm-led-orchestration-simplification.md

Add regression coverage and verification for the simplified LLM-led orchestration model.

Scope:
- update unit and integration tests so they assert runtime happy-path uses LLM finalization rather than deterministic_primary;
- cover explicit runtime-vs-benchmark mode behavior;
- verify that empty/error tool paths still allow a relevant next step and that anti-loop protection still works;
- verify representative user flows: company facts, series info, document lookup, broad recommendation.

Implementation notes:
- remove or rewrite tests that encode the old deterministic-primary runtime contract;
- keep benchmark-specific assertions in benchmark-only tests;
- prefer assertions on public behavior and metadata, not on brittle internal step counts unless necessary.

Acceptance:
- test suite encodes the new runtime contract from RFC-021;
- representative production flows pass under the simplified orchestration model;
- benchmark-specific behavior remains covered separately from runtime behavior.

Implement RFC-021: docs/rfc/RFC-021-runtime-llm-led-orchestration-simplification.md

Goal:
- simplify production agent orchestration so that LLM is the canonical runtime orchestrator;
- keep deterministic rendering only for benchmark mode and degraded fallback;
- reduce hard-coded runtime branching in core/agent.py and system prompt.

Context:
- runtime is confirmed to use gpt-5.4, so the main issue is orchestration complexity rather than model selection;
- current production flow mixes LLM planning with hard-coded route hints, source-preference guardrails, deterministic primary finalization, and benchmark-oriented control flow;
- this makes the agent harder to reason about and creates unnecessary divergence from the intended ReAct workflow.

Scope:
- introduce explicit runtime vs benchmark mode boundaries;
- remove deterministic-primary happy path from production;
- convert routing logic from hard control flow into hints plus loop protection;
- simplify system prompt and runtime state;
- protect the new design with tests and observability updates.

Acceptance:
- production happy-path answers are finalized by LLM, not deterministic_primary;
- benchmark mode still supports deterministic rendering and compact artifacts;
- runtime keeps security and anti-loop protections;
- RFC-021 child issues are completed and linked.

Problem:
Family and leaf identifiers are now present in some state, but the RFC-027 observability model is still incomplete. We need end-to-end visibility into family/leaf/stage choice, argument validation, and fallback behavior in the final routing architecture.

Required changes:
- emit route_stage on every routed request;
- record family/leaf counters and latency/error dimensions aligned with the final route tree;
- expose argument-validation status/errors in runtime metadata/metrics;
- expose family-local vs cross-family fallback counts and route-level fallback counts;
- update replay/smoke coverage and any dashboards/runbooks needed for the final model.

Acceptance criteria:
- every routed request records selected family, selected leaf, and route stage;
- validation success/error status is observable without log spelunking;
- fallback observability distinguishes family-local fallback from explicit cross-family fallback;
- replay/tests assert the new observability fields for representative routes.

Implement the minimal RFC-023 mitigation without adding a new ASR route or backend.

Required changes:
- detect Cloudflare / challenge HTML returned through chatgpt_compat /transcribe and classify it as upstream_challenge;
- add bounded retry with short backoff only for upstream_challenge;
- normalize bot-side user messaging so Telegram users never see raw HTML-derived ASR 403 errors;
- distinguish empty ASR response from generic transport/auth errors;
- add focused unit tests for classification and retry behavior.

Acceptance:
- challenge-like HTML no longer surfaces to the user;
- intermittent upstream challenge can recover via limited retry;
- tests cover challenge classification and retry path.

Реализовать RFC-012: перевести benchmark с answer-first проверки на artifact-first algorithmic validation для детерминированных кейсов, сохранив comparison/shadow режим и небольшой legacy/hybrid basket.

Scope:
- захват structured artifacts из allowlisted tools;
- расширение runner/results schema;
- algorithmic evaluator с path-based checks;
- comparison report legacy vs algorithmic;
- direct_tool mode для дешёвых deterministic suite;
- миграция dataset;
- unit/integration/comparison tests.

Definition of done:
- deterministic benchmark cases можно валидировать без обязательного финального prose LLM;
- comparison suite показывает расхождения между старым и новым validator;
- dataset и bench tools поддерживают execution/validation modes;
- acceptance criteria RFC-012 закрыты.

Добавить bounded capture benchmark artifacts в core request path.

Что сделать:
- расширить run_meta контракт для `bench_artifacts[]` и, при необходимости, `primary_artifact`;
- добавить helper для append/update артефактов с лимитами по count/size;
- для allowlisted tools (`corp_db_search`, `doc_search`, `corp_wiki_search`) прокидывать compact structured artifact через `ToolResult.metadata`;
- в agent loop после успешного tool execution складывать artifact в run meta;
- при `return_meta=true` возвращать artifacts в `/api/chat` без ломки текущих клиентов.

Ограничения:
- только compact payloads;
- hard caps на размер и количество;
- без неограниченного сохранения сырых документов или больших preview.

Acceptance:
- artifact появляется в `meta` для успешных corp_db/doc_search вызовов;
- artifacts bounded и сериализуются в bench results;
- legacy поведение для обычных chat requests не ломается.

Расширить bench dataset/results schema под execution/validation modes и artifact-aware results.

Что сделать:
- добавить backward-compatible поддержку `execution` и `validation` блоков в dataset;
- определить schema для `agent_chat`, `direct_tool`, `agent_chat_shadow`;
- определить schema для `legacy_text`, `algorithmic`, `hybrid`, `routing_only`;
- обновить runner result row shape так, чтобы artifact data и mode metadata записывались прозрачно;
- сохранить совместимость со старыми кейсами без новых полей.

Acceptance:
- старый dataset продолжает запускаться;
- новый dataset с mode-полями валиден;
- result rows содержат достаточно данных для legacy и algorithmic evaluator.

Реализовать algorithmic evaluator для structured artifacts.

Что сделать:
- добавить compact path resolver для dotted paths и простых array projections;
- реализовать набор v1 checks: `equals`, `one_of`, `exists`, `len_gte`, `contains_any`, `all_prefix`, `number_eq`, `number_range`;
- поддержать artifact selector по tool/kind;
- встроить evaluator в current bench eval path без слома `eval_checks` и `eval_routing`;
- обеспечить понятные failure reasons.

Acceptance:
- algorithmic validator работает на artifacts из corp_db/doc_search;
- failure report объясняет отсутствие артефакта, неверный path или mismatch значения;
- legacy text evaluator продолжает работать без изменений для старых кейсов.

Добавить comparison/shadow режим для сравнения legacy answer validation и нового algorithmic validation.

Что сделать:
- реализовать comparison runner/report или отдельный `bench_compare.py`;
- считать для каждого кейса `legacy_pass`, `algorithmic_pass`, `routing_pass`, `comparison_status`;
- показывать divergence reasons;
- агрегировать latency/tokens/cost по режимам;
- сделать comparison обязательным инструментом миграции deterministic buckets.

Acceptance:
- можно получить comparison report по одному смешанному run или по двум run-файлам;
- divergence cases легко читаются;
- report показывает latency/token/cost delta между режимами.

Добавить `direct_tool` execution mode в bench runner для дешёвого deterministic benchmarking.

Что сделать:
- расширить runner поддержкой per-case direct tool execution;
- определить безопасный способ вызывать tool wrapper или tools-api напрямую для benchmark cases;
- записывать result rows так, чтобы их можно было проверять тем же algorithmic evaluator;
- гарантировать, что direct deterministic suite не требует финального LLM render.

Acceptance:
- кейсы в mode `direct_tool` выполняются без обязательного `/api/chat` final answer;
- result rows содержат artifact payload и статус;
- deterministic suite показывает нулевой или существенно сниженный LLM usage.

Мигрировать текущий benchmark dataset на новую модель validation.

Что сделать:
- перевести deterministic cases на `algorithmic` validation;
- перевести часть exact/retrieval/company-fact cases на `direct_tool`, где routing coverage не критична;
- оставить `tech-001` и `tech-002` в `hybrid` или `legacy_text` basket;
- сохранить backward compatibility и читабельность dataset;
- при необходимости ввести selectors/checks для `application_recommendation`, `portfolio`, `exact facts`, `document links`.

Acceptance:
- минимум 38 из 40 текущих кейсов используют algorithmic validation;
- legacy/hybrid basket явно выделен и мал;
- dataset не теряет intent/routing coverage там, где она нужна.

Добавить unit, integration и comparison tests для RFC-012.

Что сделать:
- unit tests для path resolver и algorithmic checks;
- tests для routing + artifact selector interplay;
- integration tests для artifact capture в `/api/chat` meta;
- tests для `direct_tool` result rows;
- comparison tests на expected divergences: missing artifact, paraphrased prose, wrong artifact with plausible text.

Acceptance:
- новый evaluator и comparison mode покрыты тестами;
- artifact capture regression ловится автоматически;
- direct_tool mode и backward compatibility dataset schema проверяются тестами.

Implement RFC-023 hardening for the existing chatgpt_compat /transcribe path after the minimal mitigation is in place.

Required changes:
- add structured log fields for backend_mode, credential_id, upstream_status, error_class, and challenge_detected;
- expose counters/traces for transcribe success, failure, and challenge rate over time;
- add cooldown or quarantine behavior for credentials that repeatedly hit upstream_challenge;
- add operator-visible health/diagnostic surfaces for degraded credentials and challenge rate.

Acceptance:
- operators can identify which credential and backend mode produced a transcribe failure;
- repeated challenge on a single credential temporarily removes it from rotation;
- metrics/logs make challenge incidents visible without manually reading HTML payloads.

Problem:
The current selector payload is improved but still exposes both grouped families and a flat route list. RFC-027 calls for a compact business route tree where the selector reasons over families and leafs, not a flat peer catalog. The runtime also needs an explicit family-local fallback policy so leaf retries stay bounded inside the chosen family by default.

Required changes:
- make the selector prompt/contract tree-first: family cards with leaf entries as the primary public selector surface;
- remove the flat peer-catalog contract from the selector-facing payload in normal production mode;
- define explicit family-local fallback metadata and runtime rules;
- ensure cross-family fallback is opt-in, rare, and declared explicitly in route metadata;
- keep compatibility helpers internal if needed, but do not present the selector with a flat list of unrelated routes.

Acceptance criteria:
- selector-facing contract is route-tree-only in the default production path;
- every active leaf is attached to exactly one explicit business family in selector payloads;
- family-local fallback rules are represented in route metadata/runtime state and tested;
- cross-family fallback requires explicit declaration and is not the default recovery path;
- tests cover family/leaf membership and family-local fallback boundaries.

Parent: totosha-7h9
RFC: docs/rfc/RFC-021-runtime-llm-led-orchestration-simplification.md

Implement explicit execution mode separation for the agent.

Scope:
- introduce a clear runtime-vs-benchmark execution mode boundary in core;
- make the chosen mode visible in request metadata and observability;
- ensure runtime mode is the default for normal /api/chat traffic;
- ensure benchmark-specific artifacts and deterministic rendering are only enabled through the benchmark/degraded path.

Implementation notes:
- review core/api.py, core/agent.py, core/run_meta.py, and core/tool_output_policy.py;
- prefer one canonical mode flag instead of scattered booleans;
- avoid changing tool contracts beyond what is required for the mode boundary.

Acceptance:
- normal /api/chat requests run in runtime mode by default;
- benchmark runs can still request benchmark mode explicitly;
- observability/meta makes the execution mode visible;
- no production happy-path depends on benchmark-only mode state.

Keep skills in production runtime, but reposition them as a secondary capability layer so they expand agent abilities without competing with first-line corporate retrieval tools.

Problem:
- skills are valuable and should remain available;
- however, current skill mentions encourage list_directory/read_file loading as a normal first step, which increases the chance of unnecessary raw-browse behavior in standard corporate Q&A.

Scope:
- update core/src/agent/system.txt so the runtime policy explicitly says: use high-level corporate tools first when they fit; use skills when the task genuinely needs specialized capability or there is no suitable standard tool;
- update tools-api/src/skills.py skill mentions text so it does not frame raw skill browsing as the default opening move;
- keep skill visibility in runtime prompt intact;
- ensure the runtime still supports skills as an extensibility mechanism for future capabilities.

Acceptance:
- skills remain present in the runtime prompt;
- prompt text no longer nudges the model toward list_directory/read_file before using corp_db_search or doc_search for ordinary corporate retrieval;
- tests demonstrate that the presence of skills does not force skill-first behavior for company facts or recommendation flows.

Clean up benchmark/degraded fallback behavior so benchmark-specific logic remains isolated, correct, and aligned with the post-RFC runtime contract.

Problem:
- deterministic fallback currently loses route-specific args for document routes, such as preferred_document_ids;
- benchmark evaluation still reads metadata that production runtime no longer guarantees, which can silently hide regressions.

Scope:
- update deterministic/degraded fallback logic so route-specific args are preserved for doc routes before falling back to generic intent defaults;
- ensure benchmark-only deterministic paths continue to work without influencing production runtime behavior;
- align bench/bench_lib.py with the current runtime meta contract so missing fields do not silently degrade signal quality;
- prefer explicit benchmark-mode behavior over hidden runtime coupling.

Acceptance:
- benchmark/degraded fallback for document routes preserves preferred_document_ids and other route-specific args when available;
- benchmark evaluator no longer silently converts removed runtime meta into false negatives/false positives;
- production runtime remains unaffected by benchmark-only logic except where explicitly intended.

Parent: totosha-7h9
RFC: docs/rfc/RFC-021-runtime-llm-led-orchestration-simplification.md

Simplify the agent system prompt and runtime state so they describe policy, not an execution tree.

Scope:
- shorten core/src/agent/system.txt by removing deeply nested route-specific orchestration rules that duplicate Python logic;
- keep source-of-truth policy, safety rules, and source-priority principles;
- reduce routing_state in core/agent.py to a smaller canonical set of execution facts;
- demote low-value derived fields to debug-only or remove them.

Implementation notes:
- preserve Russian UX/tone requirements and corporate source policy;
- do not break existing tool selection just because the prompt becomes shorter;
- prefer a few generic principles over many intent-specific branches.

Acceptance:
- system prompt is materially shorter and easier to audit;
- runtime state contains a smaller canonical set of fields;
- production behavior still respects source authority and security constraints.

Parent: totosha-7h9
RFC: docs/rfc/RFC-021-runtime-llm-led-orchestration-simplification.md

Remove deterministic-primary finalization from the normal production happy path.

Scope:
- audit core/agent.py for deterministic_primary and deterministic tool renderers used during normal successful retrieval;
- keep deterministic fallback only for degraded scenarios such as empty LLM completion or transport failure;
- return successful tool payloads back into the LLM loop so the model performs final answer synthesis.

Implementation notes:
- preserve security and iteration limits;
- avoid reintroducing benchmark leakage into runtime output;
- finalizer_mode should reflect real behavior: llm for happy-path, deterministic_fallback only for degraded mode.

Acceptance:
- successful corp_db_search/doc_search happy-path requests are finalized through the normal LLM answer step;
- deterministic_primary is not used in runtime happy-path;
- degraded fallback still works when LLM returns no usable completion.

Problem:
Sphere-driven questions still overlap semantically. RFC-027 requires category-by-sphere and realized-projects-by-sphere to be separate question types with stable routing. Review checks showed that some category questions can still drift into portfolio behavior.

Required changes:
- tighten routing signals and route contracts so curated categories by sphere and portfolio projects by sphere stop competing unnecessarily;
- ensure sphere/category asks land on sphere_category_mapping broad/specialized leaves;
- ensure realized-project/reference asks land on portfolio leaves;
- add broad family-level sphere routes where needed so generic sphere questions do not get forced into the wrong specialized leaf.

Acceptance criteria:
- “Какие категории подходят для РЖД?” routes to the sphere_category_mapping family and curated-categories leaf or its accepted broad family leaf;
- “Какие есть реализованные проекты для РЖД?” routes to the portfolio family and portfolio-projects leaf or its accepted broad family leaf;
- routing remains stable across inflected/common sphere phrasing;
- tests cover both positive and anti-confusion cases.

Problem:
The current codes leaf is still closer to “codes by model name” than to the RFC-027 contract. RFC-027 expects a first-class codes/SKU route that can handle specific code systems and reverse lookup directions cleanly.

Required changes:
- add route-local schema support for exact code-oriented arguments and lookup direction/mode;
- support lamp/model -> code and code -> lamp flows explicitly;
- avoid collapsing concrete code questions back into generic catalog lookup when the question is clearly about ETM/ORACL/article/SKU semantics;
- preserve compact schemas and keep large code domains out of enums.

Acceptance criteria:
- the codes/SKU route contract supports concrete code fields and an explicit lookup mode or equivalent bounded discriminator;
- queries like “Какой ETM-код у NL Nova?” route to the codes_and_sku family;
- reverse questions like “Что это за модель по коду ...?” route to the codes_and_sku family;
- tests cover by-name, by-code, and reverse lookup cases without drifting to generic catalog lookup.

Add regression coverage for the simplified routing design with skills preserved.

Scope:
- add routing catalog tests for representative broad recommendation queries such as stadium, warehouse, and airport;
- add runtime/guardrail tests showing that shortlist-based routing allows proper tool choice while still blocking premature raw browse behavior;
- add tests proving that skills remain visible but do not force skill-first behavior for ordinary corporate Q&A;
- add benchmark/degraded tests for preserving route-specific document args and for the updated benchmark meta contract.

Acceptance:
- representative recommendation, document lookup, and company-fact scenarios are covered;
- regression tests fail on the current bad behaviors and pass on the intended design;
- the new suite protects the follow-up graph acceptance criteria end to end.

Follow-up to RFC-021 focused on making routing simpler, more reliable, and more efficient while preserving skills as a first-class extensibility mechanism.

Goal:
- keep LLM as the runtime orchestrator;
- preserve skills in production runtime, but move them to a secondary capability layer instead of letting them compete with first-line corporate retrieval flows;
- replace fragile single-winner routing with an intent-aware shortlist;
- keep only minimal guardrails in runtime;
- maintain a strict separation between production runtime behavior and benchmark-specific behavior.

Why this follow-up is needed:
- broad recommendation queries regressed because a single global route scorer lets live doc routes outrank corp application recommendation routes for non-document queries;
- benchmark/degraded fallback lost route-specific doc args such as preferred_document_ids;
- benchmark evaluation still depends on runtime metadata that is no longer guaranteed in production mode;
- the current solution should be simplified further without removing the powerful skills mechanism.

Target design:
- routing returns a primary candidate plus secondary candidates, not a single hard winner;
- intent families bias scoring, but do not hard-code a single mandatory path;
- corp high-level tools remain the default first-line retrieval layer for corporate Q&A;
- skills remain available and visible to the model, but are framed as specialized capabilities to use when needed, not as a default raw-browse path;
- benchmark-only deterministic behavior remains isolated from production runtime.

Acceptance:
- broad recommendation flows such as stadium/warehouse/airport prefer corp application recommendation over unrelated doc routes unless the user explicitly asks for a document/norms lookup;
- runtime prompt and routing keep skills available without encouraging skill/file browsing ahead of high-level retrieval tools;
- benchmark fallback preserves route-specific document args;
- benchmark evaluator no longer silently relies on removed runtime-only metadata;
- all changes are covered by regression tests.

Replace the current global single-winner route selection with an intent-aware shortlist that is simple, explainable, and robust.

Problem:
- today a single route candidate wins globally across corp_table, corp_script, and doc_domain routes;
- live doc routes can overmatch broad recommendation queries because their generated keywords/topics/patterns are too competitive;
- this creates regressions such as stadium recommendation queries selecting sports norms documents.

Scope:
- update core/documents/routing.py so route selection returns a primary candidate plus secondary candidates instead of treating one winner as a quasi-decision;
- introduce a small set of intent families sufficient for routing bias, for example: company_fact, catalog_lookup, application_recommendation, portfolio_lookup, document_lookup, other;
- make scoring intent-aware instead of purely global;
- preserve strong preference for doc_domain only for explicit document requests and document-domain language;
- ensure broad recommendation intents bias corp_db.application_recommendation ahead of unrelated doc routes;
- reduce the impact of auto-generated live-doc metadata in the global scorer so that tags/topics/summary do not overpower non-document intents;
- keep the route output simple and observable.

Non-goals:
- do not introduce new alias tools;
- do not remove live document routing;
- do not hard-code a single mandatory tool path.

Acceptance:
- select_route for representative broad recommendation queries such as stadium/warehouse/airport returns corp application recommendation as primary candidate unless the query is explicitly document-oriented;
- document lookup queries still return doc_search routes as primary candidate;
- route output contains a stable shortlist structure that runtime can consume directly;
- routing catalog tests cover the new scoring behavior.

Цель: дать боту возможность отправлять голосовые сообщения на ChatGPT transcription endpoint без отдельного ASR-ключа и без прямого выхода бота во внешние API.

Контекст:
- сейчас CLIProxyAPI хранит все нужные credentials для Codex/ChatGPT auth, но не публикует endpoint для транскрибации;
- project proxy умеет проксировать LLM-маршруты, но не умеет /transcribe;
- бот должен продолжать работать через один внутренний proxy endpoint.

Ожидаемый результат:
- CLIProxyAPI принимает запрос на внутренний endpoint транскрибации и сам ходит в ChatGPT backend;
- project proxy пробрасывает /transcribe в CLIProxyAPI;
- бот/админка могут использовать ASR URL вида http://proxy:3200 без новых внешних секретов;
- есть smoke-проверка и понятный runbook по деплою.

Ниже дочерние задачи разбивают работу на минимальные независимые шаги.

Реализовать в CLIProxyAPI отдельный endpoint для ChatGPT-style transcription.

Что сделать:
- зарегистрировать публичный маршрут POST /transcribe;
- принять multipart/form-data с аудиофайлом без изменения формата запроса со стороны клиента;
- переиспользовать существующую auth-механику Codex/ChatGPT: access_token, account_id, refresh token и логику обновления credentials;
- построить upstream URL для транскрибации из codex base URL: убрать хвост /codex и отправлять запрос на .../transcribe;
- переиспользовать уже существующие заголовки Authorization, User-Agent и Chatgpt-Account-Id;
- вернуть клиенту ответ в JSON-формате, совместимом с текущим ожиданием бота.

Критерии приёмки:
- POST /transcribe доходит до ChatGPT backend через credentials, уже хранящиеся в CLIProxyAPI;
- не требуется новый внешний секрет в bot/proxy;
- ошибки upstream прозрачно маппятся в HTTP-ответ CLIProxyAPI с диагностикой в логах.

После появления endpoint в CLIProxyAPI нужен минимальный набор проверок, чтобы обновления upstream не ломали транскрибацию незаметно.

Что сделать:
- добавить smoke-проверку для POST /transcribe с тестовым или фиктивным аудиофайлом;
- проверить базовые негативные сценарии: отсутствует файл, невалидный multipart, просроченный access token, upstream 4xx/5xx;
- убедиться, что логирование не раскрывает бинарное содержимое аудио и чувствительные токены;
- зафиксировать ожидаемый формат успешного ответа и формат ошибки.

Критерии приёмки:
- есть воспроизводимая команда или автотест, которым можно проверить /transcribe после обновления CLIProxyAPI;
- ошибки различимы и пригодны для диагностики;
- тесты покрывают как минимум happy path и один auth failure path.

Добавить в project proxy минимальный маршрут для транскрибации, не перенося в него auth-логику ChatGPT.

Что сделать:
- зарегистрировать POST /transcribe в proxy рядом с текущими служебными и /v1-маршрутами;
- принять raw multipart body и пробросить его в http://cli-proxy-api:8317/transcribe;
- сохранить необходимые входящие заголовки и корректно выставить timeout/ошибки proxy уровня;
- не дублировать в proxy access_token, account_id и refresh-логику: proxy должен оставаться тупым форвардером.

Критерии приёмки:
